(A Note on Sources) Tj T*
(Where I cite scientific findings, I have tried to be accurate about what the) Tj T*
(research actually demonstrates and careful about the distinction between) Tj T*
(peer-reviewed findings and practitioner frameworks. Several chapters deal with) Tj T*
(frameworks ? behavioral profiling, cold reading techniques, compliance language ?) Tj T*
(that have robust operational evidence in the field but varied support in controlled) Tj T*
(laboratory settings. I address these distinctions directly in the relevant chapters) Tj T*
(rather than either overclaiming or dismissing.) Tj T*
(I have ADHD. For most of my life I treated this as a liability. I have spent the) Tj T*
(last decade understanding it as a specialized attentional system that, once) Tj T*
(understood, produces a kind of rapid environmental scanning that is genuinely useful) Tj T*
(in performance and behavioral work. I mention it because it shapes how I see rooms,) Tj T*
