(Tension Laughter) Tj T*
(A laugh that arrives at a moment that is not genuinely funny is a cortisol discharge) Tj T*
(event. The nervous system is releasing pressure. Read it as a signal that the window) Tj T*
(is at its edge ? offer a brief social release, then continue the build.) Tj T*
(Always Trust the Body) Tj T*
(The body gives you the cortisol level before the mind processes it. A room that) Tj T*
(begins shifting ? legs recrossing, hands moving to faces, the slight disruption of) Tj T*
(stillness ? is a room telling you something. Read it and respond. The window is not) Tj T*
(permanent.) Tj T*
(Reading the Room's Cortisol Level) Tj T*
(The cortisol window is not fixed. It shifts across the duration of a performance,) Tj T*
(and it is not the same in every room. A late-night corporate crowd that has been) Tj T*
(drinking for an hour has a different threshold than a lunchtime keynote. A room that) Tj T*
(has just been through a tense morning session brings a different baseline than one) Tj T*
(arriving fresh. You cannot import a tension strategy from last week's show and apply) Tj T*
(it unchanged to this room tonight. The framework transfers. The calibration does not.) Tj T*
(What transfers is a reading discipline: the ability to identify, in real time, where) Tj T*
(this room currently sits inside the window ? and whether your last move pushed it) Tj T*
(toward the edge or deeper into it. Six visible indicators tell you what the room's) Tj T*
(cortisol is doing.) Tj T*
(Breathing Visibility) Tj T*
(When an audience is inside productive tension, their breathing rate slows visibly.) Tj T*
(Chests are not heaving. Shoulders are still. When tension exceeds the window,) Tj T*
(shallow rapid breathing appears ? visible in the upper chest, in the slight) Tj T*
(elevation of shoulders. Watch the first two rows. They read out the whole room.) Tj T*
(The Laughter Signal) Tj T*
(Any laugh that lands at a moment that is not genuinely funny is a cortisol discharge) Tj T*
(event. Not social laughter at something clever ? a nervous system releasing pressure) Tj T*
(it can no longer hold comfortably. Read it as a warning instrument: the window is at) Tj T*
(its edge. Offer a brief social release, then continue the build.) Tj T*
(Stillness Gradient) Tj T*
(A room inside the window goes progressively still ? the stillness of held breath,) Tj T*
(not boredom. If that stillness starts to fracture ? people shifting, recrossing) Tj T*
(legs, pulling at sleeves ? the tension has tipped from engaging to uncomfortable.) Tj T*
(The distinction is in the direction of movement: are they leaning in, or beginning) Tj T*
(to lean back?) Tj T*
(Phone Emergence) Tj T*
(A phone appearing in a tense moment is not rudeness. It is a nervous system looking) Tj T*
(for an exit. The audience member who pulls out their phone during your) Tj T*
(highest-tension moment is telling you their cortisol has exceeded what the social) Tj T*
(agreement currently justifies. Either the tension was not earned or it has been held) Tj T*
(too long.) Tj T*
(Self-Soothing) Tj T*
(Self-touch ? neck, face, hair, arms ? increases as cortisol rises. One or two) Tj T*
(self-soothers is noise. A wave of it moving across a section of the audience) Tj T*
(simultaneously is the room telling you something specific.) Tj T*
(Absence of Response) Tj T*
