(The dominant myth in performance is that the payoff is the performance. That the) Tj T*
(moment of resolution ? the card named, the thought revealed, the impossible thing) Tj T*
(completed ? is the event everything else is building toward. The neurobiology) Tj T*
(inverts this completely. The payoff is the least neurobiologically active moment in) Tj T*
(the sequence. The dopamine is in the build.) Tj T*
(Wolfram Schultz and colleagues demonstrated in research published in Science \(1997\)) Tj T*
(that dopamine neurons fire in response to the cue that predicts a reward, not the) Tj T*
(reward itself. Once the reward becomes reliably predicted, the dopamine response) Tj T*
(shifts backward in time ? to the signal, not the outcome. When the reward is) Tj T*
(delivered without the predictive signal, the dopamine response drops. When the) Tj T*
(signal appears without the reward, dopamine fires anyway. The brain is not) Tj T*
(responding to what happened. It is responding to what was predicted.) Tj T*
(This has a direct and underutilized implication for performance design.) Tj T*
(The Dopamine Build) Tj T*
(If dopamine fires during anticipation rather than resolution, then the most) Tj T*
(neurobiologically active and pleasurable part of a performance is the sustained) Tj T*
(build toward an uncertain outcome ? not the outcome itself. The reveal is a dopamine) Tj T*
(drop, not a spike. The build is the experience.) Tj T*
(This means: performances that move quickly to the reveal are structurally) Tj T*
(sacrificing their most powerful neurobiological moment. The performer who rushes to) Tj T*
(impress is cutting the dopamine experience short. The performer who can hold a room) Tj T*
(in sustained anticipation ? who can extend the build without losing the thread ? is) Tj T*
(extending the most pleasurable neurobiological state available to them.) Tj T*
(Premature Resolution) Tj T*
(The most common structural error in performance: resolving tension before it has) Tj T*
(reached maximum sustainable intensity. Every effect has a peak ? the moment where) Tj T*
(the combination of cortisol and dopamine produces maximum engagement. Releasing) Tj T*
(before the peak is leaving the best moment in the build unused.) Tj T*
(Intermittent Structure) Tj T*
(Variable reward schedules ? structures where the payoff arrives on an unpredictable) Tj T*
(interval ? produce stronger dopamine priming than fixed schedules. A performance) Tj T*
(that resolves at irregular intervals keeps the dopamine system more active than one) Tj T*
(that follows a predictable pattern. Vary the timing of your reveals.) Tj T*
(Performer's Note) Tj T*
(Map your next performance backward. Start with the reveal and work backward to) Tj T*
(identify the earliest moment the audience could have started anticipating it. That) Tj T*
(point ? the beginning of the anticipatory window ? is where the real performance) Tj T*
(begins. Everything before it is setup. Everything between it and the reveal is the) Tj T*
(experience.) Tj T*
