(The audience does not consciously decide to trust you. Trust ? or its absence ?) Tj T*
(arrives as a felt sense before any deliberate evaluation occurs. The limbic system) Tj T*
(runs an assessment of your behavioral signals against a set of threat and status) Tj T*
(indicators that were calibrated by evolutionary pressure over thousands of years,) Tj T*
(and it delivers a verdict before the prefrontal cortex has had time to weigh the) Tj T*
(evidence. By the time the audience is consciously deciding whether to believe you,) Tj T*
(the limbic system has already told them.) Tj T*
(This means credibility is not primarily a matter of what you say. It is a matter of) Tj T*
(what your behavior broadcasts before and while you say it.) Tj T*
(The Limbic System on Stage) Tj T*
(The limbic system is often described as the emotional brain, but that phrase is too) Tj T*
(simple to be useful. A better way to think about it is as the brain?s relevance) Tj T*
(engine ? the system that continuously evaluates whether what is happening matters,) Tj T*
(whether it is safe, and how strongly to respond. The limbic system does not) Tj T*
(deliberate. It does not weigh evidence. It fires rapidly, often before conscious) Tj T*
(awareness of what triggered it, and its output shapes every subsequent cognitive) Tj T*
(process.) Tj T*
(Thought and emotion are not separate systems taking turns. The cortex and limbic) Tj T*
(system are in continuous bidirectional communication. Emotional states shape what) Tj T*
(the cortex attends to, what it encodes, and what it retrieves. Cognitive states) Tj T*
(modulate how the limbic system interprets incoming signals. A performance that) Tj T*
(treats cognition and emotion as separate levers is working with an outdated map.) Tj T*
(The limbic system also matters because it is deeply connected to the hypothalamus,) Tj T*
(which helps regulate autonomic arousal, hormonal response, and the felt physical) Tj T*
(experience of emotion. When an audience member?s heart rate increases during a) Tj T*
(build, or their palms become warm during a reveal, that is the hypothalamic-limbic) Tj T*
(circuit operating in real time. You are not just changing what people think. You are) Tj T*
(changing what they feel in their bodies.) Tj T*
(This is why authority cannot be reduced to script alone. Before the audience has) Tj T*
(consciously decided whether to trust you, limbic systems are already running) Tj T*
(assessments based on posture, pace, stillness, vocal tone, and micro-expression.) Tj T*
(They are asking: is this person confident or anxious? Dominant or deferential? Safe) Tj T*
(or threatening? Those assessments complete before the first sentence ends.) Tj T*
