(The Three Layers of Credibility) Tj T*
(Credibility in performance operates on three simultaneous layers, and a failure on) Tj T*
(any one of them undermines the others.) Tj T*
(The first layer is competence: the audience's sense that you know what you are) Tj T*
(doing. This is established through precision ? the deliberate, controlled execution) Tj T*
(of each move ? and through the absence of hesitation that reads as uncertainty.) Tj T*
(Competence does not require explanation. It is communicated through behavior.) Tj T*
(The second layer is warmth: the audience's sense that you are genuinely interested) Tj T*
(in them rather than in performing at them. Warmth converts a technically impressive) Tj T*
(performance into an emotionally memorable one. People do not want to feel processed.) Tj T*
(They want to feel understood.) Tj T*
(The third layer is mystery: the maintenance of a frame around what you do that makes) Tj T*
(full understanding unavailable. Too much transparency about method converts) Tj T*
(astonishment into admiration. The mystery frame is not dishonesty ? it is the) Tj T*
(appropriate management of information in a performance context.) Tj T*
(The Audience Buy-In Curve) Tj T*
(Audience belief is not binary. It develops in stages. Most weak performances fail) Tj T*
(before the method ever matters because they never move the room past the first two) Tj T*
(stages. Astonishment is only available to audiences who have already reached the) Tj T*
(fourth or fifth.) Tj T*
(Stage 1 ? Permission) Tj T*
(Won through presence, introduction, and first seconds. The audience decides whether) Tj T*
(to offer attentional access.) Tj T*
(Stage 2 ? Interest) Tj T*
(Won through novelty, clarity, and immediate competence. The audience decides whether) Tj T*
(to stay actively engaged.) Tj T*
(Stage 3 ? Trust) Tj T*
(Won through composure, structure, and absence of friction. The audience decides) Tj T*
(whether to relax their protective evaluation.) Tj T*
(Stage 4 ? Investment) Tj T*
(Won through anticipation, pacing, and emotional relevance. The audience decides) Tj T*
(whether to care about the outcome.) Tj T*
(Stage 5 ? Surrender) Tj T*
