(Behavioral Profiling in Real Time) Tj T*
(What you are actually noticing when you know something is off ? and how to formalize) Tj T*
(that knowing into a deployable system.) Tj T*
(????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????) Tj T*
(What You Have Felt Before) Tj T*
(You meet someone and something is off. You cannot say what. They are speaking) Tj T*
(normally, saying reasonable things, presenting themselves entirely appropriately.) Tj T*
(And yet something is registering as wrong before you have processed enough) Tj T*
(information to justify the feeling. You leave the interaction slightly unsettled,) Tj T*
(with no evidence to point to. Later, it turns out you were right. Something was off.) Tj T*
(The question is: what did you actually notice?) Tj T*
(Or the inverse: you walk into a room and within thirty seconds you know which two) Tj T*
(people do not like each other, which person has the actual authority regardless of) Tj T*
(title, and which person in the corner will make the best volunteer. You did not) Tj T*
(analyze any of this. It arrived. That is behavioral pattern recognition operating at) Tj T*
(speed, below the level of deliberate observation, drawing on a training set built) Tj T*
(from thousands of prior social interactions.) Tj T*
(What Behavioral Profiling Is ? and Is Not) Tj T*
(Behavioral profiling is the disciplined practice of reading observable signals ?) Tj T*
(physical evidence, movement, posture, social behavior ? to build an accurate picture) Tj T*
(of how a person thinks, communicates, and makes decisions. It is not lie detection.) Tj T*
(It is not clinical diagnosis. It is a probability skill: the trained observer does) Tj T*
(not claim to know what someone is thinking. They know which signal clusters most) Tj T*
(consistently correlate with specific cognitive and emotional patterns, and they act) Tj T*
(accordingly.) Tj T*
(The difference between guessing and reading is triangulation. A single signal has) Tj T*
(twenty possible explanations. Three signals pointing the same direction have one.) Tj T*
(The Evidence Framework: T1?T4) Tj T*
(Every signal you will encounter in behavioral performance carries an implicit) Tj T*
(confidence rating. Practitioners who do not distinguish between them overclaim on) Tj T*
(weak evidence and under-use strong evidence in equal measure. The following tiers) Tj T*
(create precision where there would otherwise be habit.) Tj T*
(T1 ? Physical Evidence) Tj T*
(Read directly from the body or belongings. Objective, stable, highly reliable. Shoe) Tj T*
(wear, belt notch wear, callus distribution. Very few alternative explanations. A T1) Tj T*
(read is your anchor. Lead with it whenever you have one.) Tj T*
(T2 ? Research-Backed) Tj T*
(Supported by published behavioral science. Eye contact willingness, blink rate) Tj T*
(shifts, foot direction. Reliability is high when combined with T1 anchors. These are) Tj T*
(the workhorses of behavioral reading ? use them in clusters.) Tj T*
(T3 ? Field-Tested Pattern) Tj T*
(Observed consistently across thousands of performance and training hours. Not yet) Tj T*
(formally validated in peer-reviewed research. Use to add nuance to reads already) Tj T*
(grounded in T1 and T2. Never lead with a T3 alone.) Tj T*
(T4 ? Experimental) Tj T*
(Weak or disputed research support. Documented in the T4 Appendix. Know what they) Tj T*
(claim. Know why the claim does not hold. The practitioner who cites T4 signals in) Tj T*
(consulting contexts is a credibility risk.) Tj T*
