(The Forer Effect) Tj T*
(The tendency to accept vague, general personality statements as highly specific and) Tj T*
(personally accurate. Named after Bertram Forer \(1948\). The mechanism cold reading) Tj T*
(has exploited since the practice began: context does most of the work, content needs) Tj T*
(only to be plausible.) Tj T*
(The Four Principles of Translation) Tj T*
(You are never going in cold. The moment you can see someone, you have information.) Tj T*
(By the time they walk on stage, you have been reading them for minutes.) Tj T*
(Observation-based reading ? warm reading ? is not a compromise on cold reading. It) Tj T*
(is a better version of it. Act like it.) Tj T*
(Lead with the hit, then build the read. Resist the instinct to warm up with softer) Tj T*
(statements before landing the strong one. Your credibility is established in the) Tj T*
(first ten seconds. Lead with the sharpest read you have. Everything that follows) Tj T*
(lands harder because the audience already believes you.) Tj T*
(Watch before you speak. Before asking for verbal confirmation, look for nonverbal) Tj T*
(confirmation: a slight forward lean, a sharp blink, a micro-expression of) Tj T*
(recognition. Only ask for a verbal yes when you already know the answer is yes. The) Tj T*
(audience hears the confirmation. They never hear the read that got you there.) Tj T*
(Observe. Do not prescribe. You are reading behavior ? not directing lives. Never) Tj T*
(tell someone what to do, what their relationship means, or what their future holds.) Tj T*
(State what you see. Frame it as insight, not instruction. The moment you cross into) Tj T*
(advice, you have left performance and entered something with real consequences.) Tj T*
(Context Is Never Neutral) Tj T*
(A reading never begins at zero. The room matters. The event matters. The age of the) Tj T*
(participant matters. Their relationship to the people around them matters. The way) Tj T*
(they hold themselves while waiting matters. Even silence is not empty. Silence is) Tj T*
(behavior, and it is readable.) Tj T*
(This is why strong readers rarely rely on isolated statements. They read in context.) Tj T*
