(doses in a safe context it enhances attention and memory encoding. High cortisol) Tj T*
(combined with helplessness disrupts hippocampal function and degrades memory. The) Tj T*
(goal is excitation, not stress.) Tj T*
(ONSTAGE: The window between productive tension and aversive cortisol is narrower) Tj T*
(than most performers assume. A laugh that arrives at a moment that is not funny is) Tj T*
(not audience warmth ? it is a pressure-release event. Read it as a warning signal.) Tj T*
(CM Takeaway) Tj T*
(When the room tips over the cortisol window, do not accelerate. Offer a brief social) Tj T*
(release ? something warm and human. Then continue the build. The window recovers) Tj T*
(faster than you think.) Tj T*
(IN THE BRAIN: Dopamine neurons fire during the anticipatory cue that predicts) Tj T*
(reward, not during the reward itself. Once an outcome is reliably predicted, the) Tj T*
(dopamine response shifts backward in time to the signal. The build is the) Tj T*
(neurologically active phase.) Tj T*
(ONSTAGE: Do not rush to the reveal. The dopamine experience lives in the sustained) Tj T*
(build. A performance that moves quickly to the resolution is cutting short the most) Tj T*
(pleasurable neurobiological state available.) Tj T*
ET

