(Field Notes · Memory and Embodiment) Tj T*
(IN THE BRAIN: The hippocampus encodes emotionally tagged experiences with greater) Tj T*
(fidelity than emotionally neutral ones. The amygdala acts as the emotional tagger:) Tj T*
(events with high emotional valence get encoded more deeply and retrieved more easily.) Tj T*
(ONSTAGE: The most memorable moment in your performance is not the most technically) Tj T*
(impressive one. It is the one that generated the highest combined cortisol and) Tj T*
(dopamine response. Design for emotional intensity, not technical complexity.) Tj T*
(CM Takeaway) Tj T*
(Identify the single moment in each performance that should be the most emotionally) Tj T*
(intense. Design backward from it. Everything before it is build. Everything after it) Tj T*
(is resolution.) Tj T*
(IN THE BRAIN: The principle of embodied emotion holds that physical posture and) Tj T*
(gesture partially constitute emotional states rather than merely expressing them. A) Tj T*
(room of people standing experiences a different emotional reality than a room seated.) Tj T*
(ONSTAGE: Use body position as a design variable. Standing audiences are more) Tj T*
(available for emotional contagion. Seated audiences in close quarters are more) Tj T*
(receptive to intimate suggestion. Your own posture shapes your internal state as) Tj T*
(much as the audience's.) Tj T*
(CM Takeaway) Tj T*
(Before you adjust your performance, adjust your posture. The state you are in) Tj T*
(physically determines the state you perform from. This is not metaphor. It is how) Tj T*
(the nervous system works.) Tj T*
(· · ·) Tj T*
(Field Notes · Influence and Compliance) Tj T*
(IN THE BRAIN: Beliefs the audience discovers for themselves feel self-generated.) Tj T*
(Self-generated conclusions are defended as personal convictions. Conclusions) Tj T*
(delivered directly produce polite acknowledgment. The self-attribution principle) Tj T*
(means the most durable influence is the influence the person does not notice) Tj T*
(arriving.) Tj T*
(ONSTAGE: Never tell an audience what to conclude. Create the conditions for the) Tj T*
(conclusion to emerge. The insight they discover themselves will outlast anything you) Tj T*
(tell them by years.) Tj T*
(CM Takeaway) Tj T*
(Design the sequence so the conclusion arrives before you name it. When the audience) Tj T*
(has reached the insight, name it. Not before.) Tj T*
(IN THE BRAIN: Compliance is behavioral conformity driven by external pressure. It) Tj T*
(lasts as long as the authority is present. Internalization is behavioral change the) Tj T*
(person attributes to their own values. It lasts indefinitely. These are) Tj T*
(distinguishable mechanisms with distinguishable outcomes.) Tj T*
(ONSTAGE: In corporate contexts, the goal is internalization, not compliance. If) Tj T*
(participants leave having been shown something impressive, you have entertained) Tj T*
(them. If they leave having discovered something about how they behave, you have) Tj T*
(changed them.) Tj T*
(CM Takeaway) Tj T*
(Design for internalization. The test: would the behavioral shift persist if you had) Tj T*
(never told them anything? If yes, you have produced internalization. If it requires) Tj T*
(your continued presence or authority, you have produced compliance.) Tj T*
(· · ·) Tj T*
