(introduction then confirms.) Tj T*
(The credibility sequence in boardroom contexts: demonstrate before explaining, name) Tj T*
(what happened accurately, then invite their framework before offering yours. This) Tj T*
(sequence prevents the most common failure mode in executive rooms ? positioning) Tj T*
(yourself as the expert before you have earned that position from them.) Tj T*
(Corporate Audience Signals) Tj T*
(Arms crossed usually signals reserve, not hostility. Lateral eye movement before) Tj T*
(responding means they are analyzing. Phone checking means the default mode network) Tj T*
(is active ? increase personal specificity immediately.) Tj T*
(The Credibility Sequence) Tj T*
(1. Demonstrate before explaining. 2. Name what happened accurately. 3. Invite their) Tj T*
(framework before offering yours.) Tj T*
(The Real Power Map) Tj T*
(In executive rooms, formal authority and social authority are often different) Tj T*
(people. The person others glance at before they respond ? the one whose reactions) Tj T*
(calibrate the room's reaction ? is the room's real anchor. This person may or may) Tj T*
(not have the senior title. Identify them in the first two minutes. Earn them early.) Tj T*
(Once you have their engagement, the room follows.) Tj T*
(When the goal shifts from entertainment to behavioral change, the performance) Tj T*
