(FIELD STORY · PENTAGON, ARLINGTON VA) Tj T*
(The Room That Decided in Ninety Seconds) Tj T*
(On working with a defense agency leadership team) Tj T*
(I had been told before I arrived that the group would be challenging. Fourteen) Tj T*
(senior leaders in a room that had hosted briefings at the highest levels of) Tj T*
(government. They had been sent to a leadership resilience training, which meant none) Tj T*
(of them had chosen to be there. The potential for a politely hostile room was) Tj T*
(significant.) Tj T*
(I arrived forty minutes early. I walked the space, adjusted two chairs slightly,) Tj T*
(moved a water pitcher to create a small asymmetry in the table setup, and noted) Tj T*
(where the natural eyeline from the primary seating cluster would land when I stood) Tj T*
(at the front. These were small adjustments with real neurobiological implications. I) Tj T*
(was establishing the spatial anchors of the space before anyone else was in it.) Tj T*
(When the group arrived, I did not stand at the front of the room. I stood at the) Tj T*
(back, near the door, and let the group settle into their seats before any formal) Tj T*
(introduction was made. This positioning ? slightly outside the expected frame ?) Tj T*
(created a low-level salience event before I had spoken a word. Several people) Tj T*
(glanced at me twice.) Tj T*
(When I finally moved to the front and began, I did not introduce myself or) Tj T*
(acknowledge the room's reluctance. I began directly with a behavioral demonstration) Tj T*
(? specifically, a compliance sequence that every person in the room participated in) Tj T*
(without realizing it until I named it afterward. The room decided in ninety seconds.) Tj T*
(Not based on what I said. Based on what I demonstrated I could see.) Tj T*
("The room decided in ninety seconds. Not based on what I said. Based on what I) Tj T*
(demonstrated I could see.") Tj T*
() Tj T*
(FIELD STORY · TECHNOLOGY FIRM, WASHINGTON D.C.) Tj T*
(The Skeptic in the Second Row) Tj T*
(On earning the most resistant person in the room) Tj T*
(Every room has one. The person who crossed their arms before I started, who makes) Tj T*
(eye contact with their colleague rather than with me when I say something designed) Tj T*
(to land, who laughs slightly too precisely at the moments they have decided are the) Tj T*
(tricks. I am not threatened by this person. I am genuinely grateful for them. They) Tj T*
(are telling me exactly what I need to know.) Tj T*
(At a leadership keynote for a technology company in D.C., the skeptic was) Tj T*
(immediately identifiable. She was in the second row ? not the front. People who want) Tj T*
(to control their distance from the performance sit where they can observe and exit.) Tj T*
(She had a legal pad open and was writing before I started, which told me two things:) Tj T*
(she processes analytically, and she had decided to document rather than participate.) Tj T*
(I made a specific decision. I would not attempt to dismantle her skepticism) Tj T*
(directly. Direct challenges to skepticism strengthen it ? the psychological) Tj T*
(reactance literature is unambiguous on this point. Instead, I would include her in a) Tj T*
(sequence that required her analytical strengths to function correctly, and let the) Tj T*
(experience be its own argument. By the end of the first forty minutes she had put) Tj T*
(down the legal pad. I never challenged her. I invited her into an experience she) Tj T*
(could not easily explain and let the explanation be her own project.) Tj T*
("I never challenge a skeptic. I invite them into an experience they cannot easily) Tj T*
(explain and let the explanation be their own project.") Tj T*
ET

