(FIELD STORY · FINANCIAL SERVICES, NEW YORK) Tj T*
(When the Method Becomes the Message) Tj T*
(On running a behavioral influence training for a trading floor leadership team) Tj T*
(The request came through a chief people officer I had worked with the previous year.) Tj T*
(She wanted something for twelve managing directors: a half-day program on reading) Tj T*
(people in high-stakes negotiations. The group had one thing in common ? they were) Tj T*
(all exceptionally good at detecting when they were being sold something.) Tj T*
(I designed the session around a single organizing principle: I would not tell them) Tj T*
(anything I had not already demonstrated on them. Every conceptual framework they) Tj T*
(received would arrive after they had experienced its mechanism directly, in the) Tj T*
(room, without knowing it. The first forty minutes of the session were, unbeknownst) Tj T*
(to them, the demonstration itself. I was gathering behavioral baselines, testing) Tj T*
(compliance thresholds, and mapping the social hierarchy of the group through the) Tj T*
(structure of what they believed was an introductory conversation.) Tj T*
(When I revealed this, walking them through exactly what I had noticed about each) Tj T*
(person and what it suggested about their negotiation profile, the reaction was not) Tj T*
(defensiveness. It was fascination. When the person who was most resistant becomes) Tj T*
(the person asking the deepest question, the experience worked.) Tj T*
("When the person who was most resistant becomes the person asking the deepest) Tj T*
(question, the experience worked.") Tj T*
() Tj T*
(FIELD STORY · HEALTHCARE NATIONAL CONFERENCE) Tj T*
(Three Hundred People and Thirty Seconds of Silence) Tj T*
(On engineering a shared experience in a large room) Tj T*
(Three hundred people. A national healthcare conference. The audience was composed) Tj T*
(almost entirely of professionals who spend their working lives in high-stakes human) Tj T*
(interactions ? physicians, nurses, clinical administrators ? and who are, as a) Tj T*
(result, unusually attuned to emotional authenticity. They know when something is) Tj T*
(genuine and when it is not.) Tj T*
(I opened the performance with a memory exercise. I asked the full room to close) Tj T*
(their eyes, and I guided them through a thirty-second recall of a specific memory.) Tj T*
(Not an important one. A small one. The kind that surfaces unprompted at odd moments) Tj T*
(for no apparent reason. I gave them the thirty seconds. The room was completely) Tj T*
(silent.) Tj T*
(Then I described, in specific detail, three categories of memory that the exercise) Tj T*
(reliably surfaces in groups: a childhood space that no longer exists, a person seen) Tj T*
(briefly who was never spoken to, and something small that was lost and never) Tj T*
(recovered. I did not claim to be reading minds. I did not explain the mechanism. The) Tj T*
(room was already inside the experience.) Tj T*
("Accuracy is impressive. Precision that feels inevitable is something else entirely.) Tj T*
(That is the difference worth chasing.") Tj T*
