(reasoning, or experience. Compliance ends when the authority leaves. Internalization) Tj T*
(persists indefinitely. If you want to make a difference that outlasts your invoice,) Tj T*
(you want internalization.) Tj T*
(The performer in a corporate context has no formal authority whatsoever. This is,) Tj T*
(paradoxically, a meaningful advantage. Because there is no manager or compliance) Tj T*
(officer, influence cannot be attributed to hierarchy. Any change in perspective that) Tj T*
(occurs in the room has to be attributed by the audience to their own reasoning. They) Tj T*
(thought of it themselves. They will defend it accordingly.) Tj T*
(Compliance vs. Internalization) Tj T*
(Compliance: behavioral conformity from external pressure. It lasts as long as the) Tj T*
(authority is present. Internalization: behavioral change attributed by the person to) Tj T*
(their own values. It lasts indefinitely. Design for the second one.) Tj T*
(The Self-Attribution Principle) Tj T*
(Beliefs the audience discovers feel self-generated. Self-generated conclusions are) Tj T*
(defended as personal convictions. Telling a room what to conclude produces polite) Tj T*
(acknowledgment. Creating the conditions for them to find it produces ownership.) Tj T*
("Never tell an audience what to conclude. Create the conditions for the conclusion) Tj T*
(to emerge. The insight they discover themselves will outlast anything you tell them) Tj T*
(by years.") Tj T*
(The Reflection Protocol) Tj T*
(The most practical tool for creating self-attributed insight is reflection. Not) Tj T*
(agreement ? reflection. When you restate what someone has just expressed, with) Tj T*
(slightly more clarity and precision than they managed, two things happen) Tj T*
(simultaneously. They feel accurately understood ? which opens rather than closes) Tj T*
(receptivity. And they hear their own thinking returned in a form that is a small) Tj T*
(step ahead of where they started. The next observation they make builds on the) Tj T*
(reflected version, not the original. You are not pushing. You are feeding the logic) Tj T*
(they are already running.) Tj T*
(The Mirror Technique) Tj T*
(Listen. Restate with 10% more clarity. Pause. Let them confirm or correct. The) Tj T*
(confirmation is the open door. Walk through it slowly.) Tj T*
(Reactance) Tj T*
(Direct challenge to resistance strengthens it. The brain treats a challenge to its) Tj T*
(position as a threat, and threat activates defense. Do not argue. Build an) Tj T*
(experience the resistance has no mechanism to block.) Tj T*
(Timing the Name) Tj T*
(The recognition look has a short half-life. Once it passes, the moment for naming) Tj T*
(has passed with it. Train yourself to deliver the framework in under fifteen seconds) Tj T*
(when you see it. Then stop.) Tj T*
(Why This Leads to Ethics) Tj T*
(Everything in this chapter is about creating the conditions for change rather than) Tj T*
(instructing it. The self-attribution principle, the reflection protocol, the) Tj T*
(patience to hold back the named framework until the audience has arrived at it) Tj T*
(themselves ? these are not just more effective than direct instruction. They are) Tj T*
(more honest. The participant is not being directed to a conclusion. They are being) Tj T*
(accompanied toward one.) Tj T*
(That distinction is where ethics enters. Because these tools are powerful enough) Tj T*
(that the distinction matters. The same techniques that facilitate genuine insight) Tj T*
