(CHAPTER 27) Tj T*
(Audio as Architecture) Tj T*
(What plays before you enter, during transitions, and at the close is not logistics.) Tj T*
(It is some of the highest-leverage design available.) Tj T*
(????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????) Tj T*
(Most performers treat audio as background. What plays before they enter, what fills) Tj T*
(the transition between segments, what accompanies the close. These are treated as) Tj T*
(logistics. They are actually some of the highest-leverage design decisions) Tj T*
(available, and they operate on the audience neurobiologically before conscious) Tj T*
(attention is engaged.) Tj T*
