(movements: an opening theme that establishes emotional territory, transitional) Tj T*
(passages that maintain continuity between segments, a silence architecture that) Tj T*
(gives weight to key moments, and a closing theme that returns the audience to a) Tj T*
(state you have previously attached to a specific emotional experience.) Tj T*
(Pre-show music running 60?70 BPM creates mild relaxed engagement ? the) Tj T*
(neurobiological substrate of open, receptive attention. The music that feels right) Tj T*
(in your living room is not always the music that works in the room. Test it in the) Tj T*
(space, at volume, before the audience arrives.) Tj T*
(Tempo and Trust) Tj T*
(Audiences unconsciously sync physiological state to music tempo. Pre-show music) Tj T*
(running 60-70 BPM creates mild, open attentional engagement. This is available,) Tj T*
(costs nothing, and most performers do not use it.) Tj T*
