(The Opening Read) Tj T*
(The opening read establishes your credibility before you ask for anything. It is the) Tj T*
(read that makes everything after it easier. Get this right and the audience will) Tj T*
(believe the next fifteen minutes almost regardless of what happens in them.) Tj T*
(An opening read is not a warm-up. It is the first moment of the performance. Its job) Tj T*
(is not to impress ? it is to make the audience feel, in the first ten seconds, that) Tj T*
(you actually see them. That feeling is the foundation of every effect that follows.) Tj T*
(The T1 Opener) Tj T*
(Lead with a physical evidence read. T1 signals require no conversation, no setup,) Tj T*
(and no interpretation ? they are facts anchored to the body. The precision reads as) Tj T*
(impossible to anyone who met you thirty seconds ago. 'I want to start with you) Tj T*
(specifically ? not because of anything you've said, but because of something I) Tj T*
(noticed when you walked in. You've been on your feet most of today. Not because you) Tj T*
(had to be ? because that's how you think.' [Anchored to: shoe sole wear pattern,) Tj T*
(trouser crease relaxation, posture shift when seated.]) Tj T*
(The Behavioral Opener) Tj T*
(Lead with a DISC-based personality read. Fast, broad, and specific enough to feel) Tj T*
(personal without requiring defense. 'You're someone who decides quickly and explains) Tj T*
(later. That's not impatience ? that's a specific kind of intelligence. The people) Tj T*
(around you don't always understand the gap between where you are and where they're) Tj T*
(still standing.') Tj T*
(The Social Opener) Tj T*
(Open with a read about the subject's social role. Particularly powerful in strolling) Tj T*
(work where the group dynamic is visible before you approach. 'Before I start ?) Tj T*
(you're not the one who organized this evening, but you're the reason most of these) Tj T*
(people are enjoying it.' [Anchored to: energy level, eye contact pattern across the) Tj T*
