(at your slowest. Then let the silence after it hold for two full seconds before you) Tj T*
(say anything else. That silence is the audience processing the impossible. '[A) Tj T*
(specific name, date, place, or private detail ? delivered with calm authority,) Tj T*
(standing completely still, eyes on the subject.]') Tj T*
(Soft Hits, Strong Hits, and the Callback) Tj T*
(A soft hit is a broad statement delivered with precision that creates recognition) Tj T*
(without demanding confirmation. It does not require a verbal yes. It invites one.) Tj T*
(The best soft hits are the ones the subject nods to before you have finished the) Tj T*
(sentence.) Tj T*
