(A strong hit is a specific statement that cannot be explained by probability or) Tj T*
(fortune-telling. It is exact. It names something. It requires a real confirmation ?) Tj T*
(and it gets one. A strong hit changes the room's understanding of what you are.) Tj T*
(Deliver one in the first three minutes of a show and every subsequent effect runs on) Tj T*
(the credibility you just built.) Tj T*
(The callback is the structural move that makes an entire show feel cohesive rather) Tj T*
(than episodic. At the end of the show ? or at a peak moment ? you return to) Tj T*
(something that was said, observed, or revealed early on, and connect it to the) Tj T*
(present moment in a way the audience did not see coming. The callback is the move) Tj T*
(that makes people say, 'He knew at the beginning.') Tj T*
('When you walked in tonight, I noticed something. I didn't say anything then. But) Tj T*
