(of apparent impossibility should be temporally and spatially separated from the) Tj T*
(moment of preparation. What the audience sees at the reveal should feel unconnected) Tj T*
(to any prior interaction they can remember.) Tj T*
(If the audience can trace a straight line from what you did to what you revealed,) Tj T*
(the structure has failed. Effective separation is measured in minutes and in) Tj T*
(intervening effects, not in spatial distance.) Tj T*
(A strong read delivered thirty minutes after it was gathered feels impossible. The) Tj T*
(same read delivered thirty seconds after it was gathered feels like a trick. The) Tj T*
(difference is entirely structural.) Tj T*
(Delay Revelation) Tj T*
