(Where Bookings Are Actually Won) Tj T*
(The performance is not where the client makes their decision. It is where they) Tj T*
(confirm it.) Tj T*
(????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????) Tj T*
(The most common mistake working performers make about their business is believing) Tj T*
(that the quality of their show is the primary factor in whether they get re-booked) Tj T*
(and referred. It is an important factor. It is not the primary one. The decision to) Tj T*
(hire a performer ? and to hire them again, and to tell other people to hire them ?) Tj T*
(is made primarily on the basis of how they were experienced as a person to work) Tj T*
(with, not just as a performer to watch.) Tj T*
(The limbic system, which governs the emotional memory that shapes future decisions,) Tj T*
(is evaluating everything: the pre-show communication, the arrival, the interaction) Tj T*
(with the client contact backstage, the ease of the logistics, the thank-you that) Tj T*
(came afterward. All of it is data. The performance is the most visible part of the) Tj T*
(data set. It is not the only part.) Tj T*
("The real decision happens before the proposal and after the show. The performance) Tj T*
(is the evidence. Everything else is the case.") Tj T*
(The Limbic Ledger) Tj T*
(The limbic system is keeping score through the entire engagement: first email,) Tj T*
(arrival, backstage interaction, how logistics went, what came after. The performance) Tj T*
(is one item on that ledger. Not the only one.) Tj T*
(The Thank-You Test) Tj T*
(A generic thank-you signals you are professional. A specific thank-you ? naming) Tj T*
(something that happened in that room ? signals you were paying attention. The second) Tj T*
(version is remembered. The first is filed and forgotten.) Tj T*
