(The Language of Authority) Tj T*
(The words you choose and the sentence structures you use are behavioral signals.) Tj T*
(????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????) Tj T*
(The words you choose and the sentence structures you use are behavioral signals. The) Tj T*
(limbic system evaluates language for indicators of certainty, in-group membership,) Tj T*
(and cognitive authority ? and it does so below the threshold of conscious awareness.) Tj T*
(Most performers pay careful attention to what they say and very little attention to) Tj T*
(how their language signals authority or undermines it.) Tj T*
(Processing Fluency) Tj T*
(Information delivered at a slower pace is judged as more credible and more) Tj T*
(intelligent. Speed suggests the speaker is unsure it will hold up. Slow down at the) Tj T*
(beginning of every significant interaction. Source: Alter & Oppenheimer \(2009\),) Tj T*
(Psychological Bulletin, 136\(4\), 568?596.) Tj T*
(Silence as Signal) Tj T*
(Silence after something important says: I am comfortable with this space. I do not) Tj T*
(need to fill it. The other person's discomfort with the silence is theirs to manage) Tj T*
(? and they will fill it with something more genuine than anything you could have) Tj T*
