(What Weak Language Sounds Like) Tj T*
(Authority is undermined not by what you say but by the structure of how you say it.) Tj T*
(Hedge words at the end of declarative statements: 'That was really good, I thought.') Tj T*
(Apology language before a direct request: 'I was just wondering if maybe we) Tj T*
(could...' Upward inflection on statements that are not questions. Each of these) Tj T*
