(positioning. You bring something to this relationship that cannot be replicated or) Tj T*
(purchased from a catalog. Behave accordingly from first contact.) Tj T*
(The Future Vision) Tj T*
(A specific, sensory image of success planted in the client's mind becomes the) Tj T*
(comparison standard. No competitor can match a future the client has already) Tj T*
(emotionally inhabited. Build it early. Let it work.) Tj T*
(Match Communication Style) Tj T*
(Mirror the client's pace, language register, and communication density. A client who) Tj T*
(communicates in dense, efficient prose wants the same in return. A client who) Tj T*
(communicates warmly and with context wants that reflected back. This is not) Tj T*
(performance. It is the most basic form of competence in any professional) Tj T*
(relationship.) Tj T*
(The Post-Show Window) Tj T*
(The most underused moment in a performing career is the forty-eight hours after a) Tj T*
(strong show. The client is still in the elevated state the performance created. The) Tj T*
