(The Three Signal Clusters) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(For the performer, the full BTE is a reference library. In practice, three clusters) Tj T*
(cover the majority of what you will encounter on stage and in close-up work.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Cluster One: Engagement Retreat) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The body is withdrawing. They have not said no ? but their limbic system already has.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Ankle Lock \(Bi\) ? DRS 2.0. Emotional restraint. Holding back a reaction or a) Tj T*
(concern. The feet are locked, the body is bracing.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Torso Tilt Away \(Tlt\) ? DRS 1.5. Physical distancing. The brain is seeking exit) Tj T*
(without verbalizing it. The torso turns before the person is consciously aware of) Tj T*
(wanting to leave.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Arm Barrier \(Bar\) ? DRS 2.0. Protective posture. A threat signal has been detected) Tj T*
(in the interaction. The arms close across the body.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Object Barrier \(Ob\) ? DRS 1.5. Using an object as a shield ? a phone, a glass, a) Tj T*
(program, a bag held in front of the body. Unconscious, reliable, and almost never) Tj T*
(managed.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Gaze Withdrawal \(Wd\) ? DRS 2.0. Attention moving away. The person is processing a) Tj T*
(concern, evaluating an exit, or managing an internal state they do not want visible.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Performance Application: When two or more retreat signals appear in a volunteer, do) Tj T*
(not push harder. The limbic system is in conflict-avoidance mode. Reframe the) Tj T*
(interaction. Create safety. Lower the stakes of participation. "You don't have to do) Tj T*
(anything you don't want to. Just stay with me for a moment." Retreat signals are) Tj T*
(information, not failure. They tell you the volunteer's nervous system needs) Tj T*
(something different from what you are currently providing.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Cluster Two: Evaluation) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(They are evaluating ? not resisting. This is the most important signal cluster to) Tj T*
(recognize correctly, because the untrained performer will read evaluation as) Tj T*
(resistance and change course at precisely the moment they should hold still.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Lip Compress \(Lc\) ? DRS 2.0. Withholding a response. Something is being processed) Tj T*
(but not yet released. The lips press together briefly.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Head Tilt \(Tlt\) ? DRS 1.5. Cognitive engagement. The brain is actively processing) Tj T*
(information. The head tilts to one side ? a reliable indicator that evaluation is) Tj T*
(underway.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Chin Stroke \(Cs\) ? DRS 1.5. Deliberation. A decision is being weighed. The hand) Tj T*
(moves to the chin and rests.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finger Steeple \(St\) ? DRS 2.5. High cognitive confidence. An opinion or judgment is) Tj T*
(forming. The fingertips press together. This is not a stress signal ? it is a) Tj T*
(processing signal.) Tj T*
ET

