(ovation cascades, audience contagion, and compliance spread. One person rising) Tj T*
(confidently lowers the threshold for everyone around them.) Tj T*
(Suggestibility    Receptiveness to ideas, suggestions, and framings offered by) Tj T*
(others. Distinct from hypnotic responsiveness, which requires specific trait) Tj T*
(absorption. General suggestibility predicts almost nothing about hypnotic) Tj T*
(responsiveness.) Tj T*
(· · ·) Tj T*
(APPENDIX A1) Tj T*
(T4 Signal Review: The Evidence Record) Tj T*
(Four signals removed from the working system ? with the research that informed their) Tj T*
(removal) Tj T*
(The following four signals are widely taught in behavioral performance and) Tj T*
(NLP-derived training contexts. Each carries a claim that sounds specific and usable.) Tj T*
(Each has also been subjected to controlled research that found the claim did not) Tj T*
(hold up in the way practitioners assumed. They are documented here ? not to discard) Tj T*
(the observational tradition that produced them, but to be precise about what the) Tj T*
(evidence actually supports.) Tj T*
(The T4 designation in this system does not mean 'false.' It means: the specific) Tj T*
(claim has not been supported in the form it is typically taught, and a practitioner) Tj T*
(who deploys it with confidence in a professional context is carrying unnecessary) Tj T*
(credibility risk. Read what the research found. Make your own judgment about how to) Tj T*
(hold the signal.) Tj T*
(SIGNAL 1 ? NLP Eye Movement Direction) Tj T*
(THE CLAIM: Eye movement direction reliably indicates whether a person is accessing a) Tj T*
(visual memory \(up-right\), constructing a visual image \(up-left\), accessing an) Tj T*
(auditory memory \(horizontal-right\), or experiencing a kinesthetic state) Tj T*
(\(down-right\). This map allows a trained observer to detect the cognitive process a) Tj T*
(person is currently engaged in.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(THE RESEARCH: Wiseman, Watt, ten Brinke, Porter, Couper, and Rankin \(2012\) published) Tj T*
(a controlled three-study examination of this specific claim in PLOS ONE. They tested) Tj T*
(whether the predicted eye-movement patterns were observable and whether they could) Tj T*
(distinguish truth-tellers from liars. The predicted patterns did not appear) Tj T*
(consistently. Eye direction did not reliably predict memory access mode. The study's) Tj T*
(conclusion was direct: the NLP eye-movement model is not supported by available) Tj T*
(evidence.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(WHAT REMAINS VALID: Deviation from an individual's established baseline is a genuine) Tj T*
(signal. If someone's eyes go somewhere different from where they normally go when) Tj T*
(answering questions, that shift is worth tracking ? not because the direction) Tj T*
(predicts a cognitive process, but because the deviation signals that something is) Tj T*
(being processed differently than usual. The baseline-deviation framework survives.) Tj T*
(The directional map does not.) Tj T*
(SIGNAL 2 ? Smooth Lower Eyelids as Confidence Indicator) Tj T*
(THE CLAIM: Smooth, relaxed lower eyelids indicate genuine confidence and authentic) Tj T*
(emotional display. Tension in the lower eyelid is a micro-leak of concealed anxiety) Tj T*
(or deception.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(THE RESEARCH: Lower eyelid tension varies significantly with age, individual) Tj T*
(physiology, hydration, fatigue, and the ambient lighting conditions in a room. The) Tj T*
(specific claim ? that smooth lower eyelids reliably indicate confidence or that) Tj T*
(lower eyelid tension reliably indicates concealment ? has not been supported in) Tj T*
ET

