(controlled facial coding research. Meta-analyses of facial deception detection,) Tj T*
(including work reviewed by Vrij and colleagues, find that no single facial indicator) Tj T*
(reliably distinguishes authentic from deceptive emotional display across individuals.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(WHAT REMAINS VALID: The Duchenne marker ? the distinction between genuine and social) Tj T*
(smiling based on orbicularis oculi involvement ? is supported and documented. That) Tj T*
(is a different and more robust signal. The lower eyelid smoothness claim as a) Tj T*
(standalone confidence indicator is not sufficiently reliable to carry real) Tj T*
(evidential weight.) Tj T*
(SIGNAL 3 ? Deep Under-Eye Wrinkles as Chronic Worry Indicator) Tj T*
(THE CLAIM: Deep wrinkles under the eyes, when permanent, indicate a lifetime pattern) Tj T*
(of chronic worry, anxiety, or emotional suppression. The wrinkle pattern encodes the) Tj T*
(person's dominant emotional baseline.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(THE RESEARCH: Under-eye wrinkle depth is primarily determined by sun exposure, skin) Tj T*
(type and genetics, hydration, sleep quality, and age ? factors that have very) Tj T*
(limited relationship to chronic emotional state. Facial aging research consistently) Tj T*
(finds that sun exposure, smoking, and sleep patterns are the dominant determinants) Tj T*
(of under-eye wrinkling. The claim that wrinkle depth encodes emotional history lacks) Tj T*
(evidential support. The signal in Paul Ekman's original research regarding permanent) Tj T*
(wrinkles relates specifically to the Duchenne marker and crow's feet from genuine) Tj T*
(smiling ? not under-eye depth as a worry indicator.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(WHAT REMAINS VALID: The principle that faces encode habitual movement is real.) Tj T*
(Crow's feet from a lifetime of genuine smiling tell a different story than their) Tj T*
(absence. But under-eye wrinkle depth as a chronic worry read is not a defensible) Tj T*
(evidence-based claim.) Tj T*
(SIGNAL 4 ? Hair Part Direction as Personality Indicator) Tj T*
(THE CLAIM: Hair parted on the left projects strength and logic, associated with) Tj T*
(dominant and authoritative personalities. Hair parted on the right projects) Tj T*
(cooperation and nurturance. Center parts indicate balance or ambivalence.) Tj T*
(Side-parting direction is a reliable indicator of dominant personality traits.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(THE RESEARCH: This claim does not appear in any peer-reviewed behavioral science) Tj T*
(literature. It originates primarily in a self-published 1999 book. No controlled) Tj T*
(studies have examined whether hair part direction correlates with personality traits) Tj T*
(in ways that generalize beyond individual styling choices. The claim that hair part) Tj T*
(direction encodes meaningful personality information is not supported by any tier of) Tj T*
(behavioral evidence currently available.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(WHAT REMAINS VALID: Nothing in this specific claim is supported. Hair styling) Tj T*
(choices do carry social information ? formality, cultural context, investment in) Tj T*
(appearance ? but the directional claim is unsupported at any evidential level. Do) Tj T*
(not use it in any professional or performance context where credibility is a concern.) Tj T*
(The practitioner who knows why T4 signals are T4 is a more credible practitioner) Tj T*
(than one who has simply been told not to use them. The evidence record exists. It is) Tj T*
(accessible. The performers most worth taking seriously in this field are the ones) Tj T*
(whose confidence is calibrated to what they can actually defend.) Tj T*
(A Note on What Gets Better) Tj T*
(The removal of T4 signals is not a loss. It is a precision upgrade. Every signal) Tj T*
(that stays in the working system is a signal you can use in a corporate briefing) Tj T*
(room, at a conference presentation, in front of an audience that includes) Tj T*
ET

